# MASTER PROMPT — BUILD FULL PYTHON DEV PLATFORM

You are a senior Python full-stack engineer.

Your task is to build a complete developer collaboration web platform using Python only.

Do NOT explain theory.
Generate full working code step by step.

The result must run locally after copy paste in VS Code.

---

# TECH STACK (MANDATORY)

Backend:

* Python 3.11+
* FastAPI
* PostgreSQL
* SQLAlchemy ORM
* OAuth via Authlib
* Jinja2 templates (server rendered)
* TailwindCSS UI
* Uvicorn server

Storage:

* Local file storage for images/videos
* Structured uploads folder

Project must be clean and modular.

---

# PLATFORM IDEA

A developer platform where devs create profiles and project pages.

They can:

* sign in with GitHub or Google
* create profile
* upload avatar
* create projects
* attach GitHub repo
* post project updates
* upload images/videos
* other devs can comment
* public project pages

Like mini GitHub + social dev hub.

---

# CORE FEATURES

## 1. Landing Page

Route: /

Clean modern dev landing page.

Sections:

* Hero text
* Login with GitHub
* Login with Google
* Explore projects button

---

## 2. OAuth Login System

Implement OAuth with:

* GitHub OAuth
* Google OAuth

On first login:
create user in database.

Store:

* id
* username
* email
* avatar
* provider

Use secure session cookies.

---

## 3. User Dashboard

After login redirect to:

/dashboard

Show:

* profile info
* edit profile button
* create project button
* list of user projects

---

## 4. User Profile Page (public)

Route:
/user/{username}

Shows:

* avatar
* name
* bio
* GitHub link
* projects
* join date

Editable by owner only.

---

## 5. Create Project

Route:
/create-project

Fields:

* project name
* description
* GitHub repo URL
* project image
* tags

Store in database.

---

## 6. Project Page (important)

Route:
/project/{id}

Show:

* project banner/image
* name
* description
* GitHub repo link
* creator
* posts feed

---

## 7. Project Posts

Inside project page creator can post:

* text update
* image upload
* video upload

Store media locally.

Show posts timeline style.

---

## 8. Comments System

Logged in users can comment on posts.

Simple threaded comments.

---

## 9. GitHub Repo Preview

When GitHub repo URL added:

Use GitHub API to fetch:

* stars
* repo name
* description
* last update

Display on project page.

---

